job_description:
Ogilvy was founded in 1948 by David Ogilvy. David created a culture that deeply respects and cares about its people and clients. Our mission is to inspire people and brands to make an impact and we are committed to attracting, growing, and retaining the best talent in the industry.&nbsp;

&nbsp;

Key Responsibilities:&nbsp;

Lead Creative Projects: Own the creative process from concept to completion, ensuring high-quality and strategically aligned output.&nbsp;

Innovate &amp; Execute: Generate impactful creative ideas, provide expert art direction/copy, and integrate AI tools to enhance efficiency.&nbsp;

Team Leadership: Mentor and guide junior creative team members, fostering a collaborative and inspiring environment.&nbsp;

Client Engagement: Present ideas effectively, build strong client relationships, and translate insights into compelling creative solutions.&nbsp;

Strategic Thinking: Understand and contribute to strategic briefs, ensuring creative work is on target and impactful.&nbsp;

Business Acumen: Contribute to&nbsp;financial management&nbsp;and ensure efficient project delivery.&nbsp;

&nbsp;

Ogilvy was founded in 1948 by David Ogilvy. David created a culture that deeply respects and cares about its people and clients. Our mission is to inspire people and brands to make an impact and we are committed to attracting, growing, and retaining the best talent in the industry.&nbsp;

Key Responsibilities:&nbsp;

Conceptualize &amp; Execute: Develop and execute compelling visual concepts and designs for integrated campaigns, ensuring high-quality craft, brand adherence, and effective communication across various platforms, especially digital and&nbsp;social.&nbsp;

Collaborate &amp; Innovate: Work closely with creative partners, managers, and clients to translate briefs into visually engaging solutions, pushing creative boundaries and exploring new techniques, including leveraging AI tools.&nbsp;

Manage &amp; Deliver: Oversee campaigns from concept to completion, managing multiple projects, meeting deadlines, and ensuring all work is delivered on time, on budget, and to the highest quality.&nbsp;

Strategic Thinking: Understand client needs, market trends, and brand values to develop strategic, insightful creative solutions.&nbsp;

Internal Relationships: Build strong relationships with internal departments (Account Management, Planning, Traffic) to ensure seamless project execution.&nbsp;

